result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel Stephen Zelms was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/ Intent-Amphetamine/Methamphetamine/etc.(>10-50g) [Modifiers: Repeater], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(e)3.
  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt:
Quashed on record 10/21/22
2 Certified copies returned from PRSO

8:48 AM Defendant Daniel Stephen Zelms appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Christopher Michael Restemayer appeared by video for Daniel Stephen Zelms.  Attorney Mark T. Fuhr  in court for State of Wisconsin. ADA Fuhr states an agreement has been reached and recites the agreement on record. All parties agree to the terms. Attorney Restemayer requests the warrant be quashed. So Ordered by the court. Court questions defendant on appearing personally. Defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently waives his right to be personally present in the courtroom. Contingent upon the defendant's plea to counts 3 and 5 the State will move to Dismiss and read in the remaining counts. DE enters plea of GUILTY to counts 3 and 5 therefore the remainder of the counts are DISMISSED and READ IN. Court questions DE regarding the plea. DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC. Comments by parties.
Court imposes:

Ct. 1- DRI 

Ct. 2- DRI

Ct. 3- State Prison (Concurrent to Ct. 5 and any other sentence in being)
2 Yrs Initial Confinement 
2 Yrs Extended Release 
Conditions of extended release:
$400 Fine inclusive of costs 
$250 DNA + Sample 
$32.50 Certified Documents Fees 
Submit to an AODA Assessment and follow through with any and all counseling recommended by probation 

Ct. 4- DRI 

Ct. 5- State Prison (Concurrent to Ct. 3 and any other sentence in being)
2 Yrs Initial Confinement 
2 Yrs Extended Release 
Conditions of extended release:
$400 Fine inclusive of costs 
Submit to an AODA Assessment and follow through with any and all counseling recommended by probation 

Ct. 6- DRI

Defendant is Eligible for both the the Challenge Incarceration and Substance Abuse Programs
Defendant is given 0 Days Sentence Credit 

Appeal Rights Given
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Plea/sentencing hearing on October 21, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Plea/sentencing hearing on December 6, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

11:00 AM DA calls case and states appearances. Defendant Daniel Stephen Zelms appeared by phone, in custody from Jackson Correctional.  Attorney Christopher Michael Restemayer appeared by video for Daniel Stephen Zelms.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. DA Kelz states this matter is set for a Preliminary hearing. Defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently waives his right to be personally present in the courtroom. Court questions defendant in regards to waiving the preliminary hearing. Preliminary Hearing waived.  Waiver accepted by the Court. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial. Information filed, acknowledged by parties and reading waived. Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts. Attorney Restemayer requests a date for Plea and Sentencing. Court questions Attorney Restemayer on Speedy Disposition filed.  Attorney Restemayer states the motion for speedy disposition is withdrawn at this time. Attorney Restemayer to contact the Judicial Assistant to set Plea and Sentencing date off record.
Ltr to Judge re: Prompt Disposition
Jury trial on October 24, 2022 at 09:00 am.
